1
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,180
[Episode 25]

2
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:45,199
<i>Sure. Wait for me a second.</i>

3
00:01:45,199 --> 00:01:46,909
<i>Sure.</i>

4
00:01:53,499 --> 00:01:55,980
<i>Hey, what have you been up to lately?</i>

5
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:58,393
<i>I've been really busy lately.</i>

6
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,040
<i>Let's have a drink.</i>

7
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:08,720
<i>Sure, no problem. I'll wait.</i>

8
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,346
<i>Okay.</i>

9
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,760
Where do you live?

10
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:14,880
I'll get someone to take you home.

11
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:21,780
Where are you going?

12
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,399
Excuse me, I want ten coins.

13
00:02:36,399 --> 00:02:37,966
Okay.

14
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,340
Ten yuan.

15
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:44,213
What do you want, exactly?

16
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:57,106
Told you I'm lucky.

17
00:03:02,399 --> 00:03:04,739
Are you leaving or not?
If not, I'm heading back.

18
00:03:04,739 --> 00:03:05,940
Wait.

19
00:03:05,940 --> 00:03:09,666
No, it's not even two hours yet.
Stay with me a little longer.

20
00:03:11,299 --> 00:03:14,960
Did you break up with your boyfriend again?
You're just sulking here, aren't you?

21
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,820
What does that have to do with this?

22
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,859
Jing.

23
00:03:21,859 --> 00:03:24,899
Did you like dolls like this as a kid?

24
00:03:24,899 --> 00:03:29,099
I thought little girls liked these.

25
00:03:30,859 --> 00:03:32,473
I don't remember.

26
00:03:41,399 --> 00:03:43,920
<i>Okay, I'll go now.</i>

27
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,753
<i>I'll be right over.</i>

28
00:03:47,699 --> 00:03:49,400
<i>Come on, Jing.</i>

29
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,179
<i>I just had an emergency
and have to handle it now.</i>

30
00:03:55,179 --> 00:03:56,380
<i>I can't take you home.</i>

31
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:59,500
<i>Use this to buy two orders of rice rolls.
Take one for Uncle Chen.</i>

32
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,959
<i>If Uncle Chen asks where I went,
you know what to say, right?</i>

33
00:04:01,959 --> 00:04:03,660
<i>I'll say you went to Aunt Liu's.</i>

34
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:06,359
<i>Right. Say that. Be good and watch your step.</i>

35
00:04:06,359 --> 00:04:09,026
<i>Take it slow on your way home. Careful now.</i>

36
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,046
<i>Hello?</i>

37
00:04:32,499 --> 00:04:34,280
Oh, come on.

38
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:02,560
Why can't I pick this up?

39
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,140
Are you done yet?

40
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:08,173
Almost, sweetie. I'm nearly done.
Just a second.

41
00:05:24,119 --> 00:05:27,740
This is for you. See? My daughter is amazing.

42
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:29,080
Jing.

43
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,220
- This is for you.
- I don't want it.

44
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:33,819
Didn't you love these as a kid? Take it.

45
00:05:33,819 --> 00:05:35,800
That was when I was a kid.

46
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,260
Let's go.

47
00:05:56,960 --> 00:06:00,033
[Lorraine Flower Kitchen]

48
00:06:06,259 --> 00:06:08,156
What did you want to see me about?

49
00:06:25,859 --> 00:06:27,499
Didn't I promise you before

50
00:06:27,499 --> 00:06:30,980
I'd buy you a gold bangle
for your wedding chest?

51
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:32,499
I was strapped for cash back then.

52
00:06:32,499 --> 00:06:35,059
Now that I'm doing better,
I should make it up to you.

53
00:06:35,059 --> 00:06:36,620
No need.

54
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:39,843
There's too much I never had.
You can't make up for all of it.

55
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,800
I went to see Chen Yi.

56
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,120
Why did you go to him?

57
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:51,056
I didn't know where you were.
Of course, I had to ask him.

58
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,953
I knew he had to know where you were.

59
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:58,760
All these years,

60
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,613
Yi has really been there for you.

61
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:09,113
Those texts I sent you were exactly how I felt.

62
00:07:10,601 --> 00:07:12,593
I'm on my own now.

63
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,700
On your own?

64
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:18,086
You haven't found someone else to lean on?

65
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:23,100
Or are you trying to come back and lean on me?

66
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,110
I have my own place in Peng City.

67
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,045
Don't underestimate me.

68
00:07:29,045 --> 00:07:34,186
If I really wanted someone to lean on,
I'd have plenty of people to care for me.

69
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:23,680
You're my daughter.

70
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:26,476
Of course, I know your temper.

71
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:31,450
I didn't expect this to make you forgive me.

72
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,203
You agreed to come see me.
That's already more than enough.

73
00:08:56,001 --> 00:08:59,606
It's been two hours. I should get going.

74
00:09:02,761 --> 00:09:05,286
There are no more buses back to Peng City now.

75
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:09,010
Which hotel are you staying at tonight?
Have you booked it?

76
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,241
The water is all in the fridge.

77
00:09:32,241 --> 00:09:34,421
Call the front desk if you need anything.

78
00:09:34,421 --> 00:09:35,861
Jing.

79
00:09:35,861 --> 00:09:38,500
Do you still have work tonight?

80
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:42,780
If you're not busy,
maybe we could stay here a bit longer.

81
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:44,820
I go to bed early now that I'm working.

82
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:46,741
I'm leaving.

83
00:09:46,741 --> 00:09:48,386
Jing.

84
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:54,890
There is one thing
I was hoping you could help me with.

85
00:09:57,780 --> 00:09:59,506
Go ahead.

86
00:10:02,054 --> 00:10:04,079
Lately,

87
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,190
I've been dreaming a lot.

88
00:10:09,901 --> 00:10:12,776
It's always about the past.

89
00:10:16,881 --> 00:10:19,136
It's about when you were little.

90
00:10:21,940 --> 00:10:24,423
About your grandparents.

91
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:31,966
In a while,

92
00:10:37,141 --> 00:10:39,740
it'll be the anniversary
of your grandma's passing.

93
00:10:41,261 --> 00:10:44,880
Could you come with me to Jiang City?

94
00:10:55,227 --> 00:10:57,920
I'm afraid to go see her alone.

95
00:11:07,213 --> 00:11:09,839
You don't have to answer right away.

96
00:11:15,001 --> 00:11:16,813
I can wait.

97
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:14,761
<i>You have a sensitive stomach.
Don't eat too much greasy takeout.</i>

98
00:12:14,761 --> 00:12:19,280
<i>If you can't get used to living away,
come home.</i>

99
00:12:26,281 --> 00:12:27,340
Save it like this.

100
00:12:27,340 --> 00:12:29,900
What do you want for dinner?

101
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:33,466
All done?

102
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,141
Let's call it a day.

103
00:12:39,141 --> 00:12:41,146
It's raining. I'll take you to your hotel.

104
00:12:41,146 --> 00:12:44,142
No, I don't want to stay at the hotel tonight.

105
00:12:48,021 --> 00:12:50,986
Then where are you going? I'll take you.

106
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:15,193
It's so late. Sorry to trouble you.

107
00:13:16,781 --> 00:13:19,281
Is that how you talk to me now?

108
00:13:19,281 --> 00:13:21,773
So polite it feels distant.

109
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:27,926
Which way?

110
00:13:27,926 --> 00:13:29,557
Right.

111
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,213
You're back.

112
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,540
Where should I put the umbrella?

113
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:33,655
Just leave it by the door.

114
00:14:38,766 --> 00:14:40,572
Why is he here?

115
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:47,460
Maybe we should go back.

116
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:50,307
We dropped by out of the blue.
We didn't even give you a heads-up.

117
00:14:50,307 --> 00:14:52,080
Are we interrupting something?

118
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,560
Not we.

119
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,233
It's you.

120
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:59,840
How is she interrupting in her own home?

121
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,660
That's not what I meant.

122
00:15:02,281 --> 00:15:04,720
I just don't think we should stay tonight.

123
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,240
What are you talking about?

124
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,890
Miao Jing, it isn't what you think.

125
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:13,070
I mean, Yi and I aren't what you think.

126
00:15:17,919 --> 00:15:19,672
Then we...

127
00:15:23,829 --> 00:15:25,060
It's getting late.

128
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:28,780
It won't be safe if you head back too late.

129
00:15:33,001 --> 00:15:35,100
Dry your hair.

130
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:40,486
I'm scared.

131
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,621
What are you scared of?

132
00:15:42,621 --> 00:15:45,100
What's wrong? Come here. Let me hold you.

133
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:46,808
What happened?

134
00:15:49,621 --> 00:15:51,393
Don't be scared.

135
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:54,960
Come here. Don't go over there. Come here.

136
00:15:57,580 --> 00:15:59,566
Did you make dinner?

137
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,580
They got soaked and need something hot.
Otherwise, they'll catch a cold.

138
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:09,090
If you haven't cooked, order delivery.

139
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:17,632
We have a hot pot at home. It'll be ready soon.

140
00:16:23,501 --> 00:16:25,886
Will you be staying for dinner too, Mr. Cen?

141
00:16:26,621 --> 00:16:29,060
- Sure.
- Mr. Cen.

142
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:30,973
Be careful on the road.

143
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,766
See you at the office tomorrow.

144
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,739
Dry your hair.

145
00:17:27,341 --> 00:17:28,818
Here.

146
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,373
Thanks.

147
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:45,340
I used to keep a first aid kit in my bedroom.
It was yours?

148
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,900
Yes.

149
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:52,570
You brought him every time you came?

150
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:59,341
When he came to my place and couldn't find me,
he'd go make trouble at the shop.

151
00:17:59,341 --> 00:18:02,641
Sometimes, when I couldn't avoid him,
I'd come here to Yi's place.

152
00:18:02,641 --> 00:18:05,661
Yi has clout, so he doesn't go too far.

153
00:18:05,661 --> 00:18:07,361
All right.

154
00:18:07,361 --> 00:18:10,601
He's just stubborn.
He doesn't really have any other flaws.

155
00:18:10,601 --> 00:18:11,861
He's actually soft-hearted.

156
00:18:11,861 --> 00:18:16,670
No matter who asks him for help,
he'll do it, even with a scowl.

157
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:19,321
That's just how he is.

158
00:18:19,321 --> 00:18:20,841
Come here. I'll dry your hair.

159
00:18:20,841 --> 00:18:22,940
Let me help.

160
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:25,316
You're hurt. You should rest.

161
00:18:28,921 --> 00:18:30,596
Come here.

162
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,100
Is it too hot?

163
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:10,321
It isn't hot now.

164
00:19:10,321 --> 00:19:11,362
It's so hot here.

165
00:19:11,362 --> 00:19:13,267
No, it's so cold now.

166
00:19:35,121 --> 00:19:36,361
It's okay.

167
00:19:36,361 --> 00:19:37,841
- Tu Li!
- Don't be afraid.

168
00:19:37,841 --> 00:19:39,141
Come out.

169
00:19:39,141 --> 00:19:40,260
- Don't be afraid.
- Let me tell you,

170
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:41,600
you can run, but you can't hide.

171
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:44,401
You shameless jerk. I'll scream.

172
00:19:44,401 --> 00:19:45,950
Come out.

173
00:19:46,621 --> 00:19:49,720
Don't worry. It's safe here.

174
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,450
I'll scream.

175
00:19:54,581 --> 00:19:55,700
It's you again.

176
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:56,760
Chen Yi.

177
00:19:56,760 --> 00:20:00,061
You keep disrespecting me.

178
00:20:00,061 --> 00:20:03,166
I'm telling you, push me too far,
and I'll bite back.

179
00:20:03,980 --> 00:20:07,321
I've still got some boiling water. Want some?

180
00:20:07,321 --> 00:20:08,960
Get lost.

181
00:20:10,032 --> 00:20:12,480
Bao, your dad is right here.

182
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:15,780
Your mom raised you like a little brother.
She's not a good mother.

183
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:18,121
Your dad will find you a new mom.

184
00:20:18,121 --> 00:20:19,641
Then you'll have a mom.

185
00:20:19,641 --> 00:20:21,713
You'll be a kid with a mom.

186
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:26,020
Yang Da Jun, have you no shame?
What nonsense are you spewing?

187
00:20:26,020 --> 00:20:27,440
Can you get out of here?

188
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:28,841
Nice going.

189
00:20:28,841 --> 00:20:30,581
Neighbors, come judge this.

190
00:20:30,581 --> 00:20:33,020
The little boy in there is my son.

191
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:34,520
They won't let me see him.

192
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:37,140
Is there no justice? Someone, judge this.

193
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:39,000
Aren't you embarrassed?

194
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,280
When have you ever treated Bao
like your own son?

195
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:46,923
Bao is my son. He's our son, right?

196
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,940
Chen Yi, don't touch me. I'll call the police.

197
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:52,540
Stop yelling nonsense out here.

198
00:20:52,540 --> 00:20:54,081
Who are you?

199
00:20:54,081 --> 00:20:56,821
You're drunk and making a scene at my door.
And you ask who I am?

200
00:20:56,821 --> 00:20:58,680
Miao Jing, go inside.

201
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:01,260
Your door? I can still speak, can't I?

202
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,801
Everyone, look at this family.

203
00:21:02,801 --> 00:21:06,700
Shameless. They're protecting this woman
and keeping me from my own son.

204
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:08,581
Did you marry her? Did you get a license?

205
00:21:08,581 --> 00:21:11,801
Did you register? Why is he your son?

206
00:21:11,801 --> 00:21:13,960
I held a wedding banquet. I paid for it.

207
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:17,540
What about the paternity test?
Otherwise, this is extortion.

208
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:19,401
Tu Li, I'm giving you two choices.

209
00:21:19,401 --> 00:21:24,280
Either give me the money,
or I'm taking the kid. Got it?

210
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:27,280
If you take my child today,
I'll fight you to the death.

211
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,861
With what? Nail clippers?

212
00:21:30,861 --> 00:21:33,460
Either give me the money,
or I'm taking the kid.

213
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,700
You're broke, right?

214
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:37,700
You gambled it all away.
Now you're here asking Tu Li for money.

215
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:40,301
Fine. I'll give you two choices today.

216
00:21:40,301 --> 00:21:45,260
Either you leave right now,
or I call the police and have you arrested.

217
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:47,600
Who are you trying to scare?

218
00:21:51,921 --> 00:21:53,861
Hello, is this the police?

219
00:21:53,861 --> 00:21:55,700
This is the power bureau's housing block.

220
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,180
- I'm reporting someone for gambling.
- Fine.

221
00:21:58,180 --> 00:21:59,280
He's right here now.

222
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,860
- Fine.
- Please get here quickly.

223
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:03,220
I've got something to do.
I'll come back another day.

224
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:04,460
- Right.
- Tu Li.

225
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:08,860
I'm telling you, Tu Li.
I'll come back for you another day.

226
00:22:14,901 --> 00:22:16,713
Thank you.

227
00:22:24,161 --> 00:22:25,401
Come here.

228
00:22:25,401 --> 00:22:27,720
Let me hold you. Look at me. It's okay.

229
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,120
It's okay. I'm here.

230
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:31,268
Mommy's here.

231
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:33,053
Don't be scared.

232
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:54,561
How did you know he was a gambling addict?

233
00:22:54,561 --> 00:22:56,460
I was bluffing.

234
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,740
That was amazing.

235
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:04,980
When I was little, no one helped me
when I got bullied.

236
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:07,341
So I learned how to scare them off myself.

237
00:23:07,341 --> 00:23:10,193
Otherwise, the trouble never ends.

238
00:23:11,401 --> 00:23:15,480
To solve a problem,
you don't always need strength or a loud voice.

239
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:18,301
You need the right approach.

240
00:23:18,301 --> 00:23:20,806
That's how you learn to stand on your own.

241
00:23:21,601 --> 00:23:26,826
After all, no one can protect someone forever.

242
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:32,693
Let's eat.

243
00:23:35,739 --> 00:23:37,000
What do you mean?

244
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,873
It's all in the drink.

245
00:23:39,821 --> 00:23:42,576
Come on, it's all in the drink.

246
00:23:48,581 --> 00:23:51,593
Does this make us a family?

247
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:55,540
Bao, don't say that.

248
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:57,341
Why can't I?

249
00:23:57,341 --> 00:24:01,540
Mom, Auntie, and me.

250
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:02,540
What about me?

251
00:24:02,540 --> 00:24:05,220
You're Auntie's Bao.

252
00:24:06,861 --> 00:24:09,341
Bao, drink your orange juice.

253
00:24:09,341 --> 00:24:10,921
You can't just say things like that.

254
00:24:10,921 --> 00:24:13,460
Then why is he my Bao?

255
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:15,871
Because you can protect him.

256
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:17,880
He's a boy. I'm a boy too.

257
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:20,921
I live with Mom. You live together, too.

258
00:24:20,921 --> 00:24:24,180
Mom is amazing. Auntie is amazing, too.

259
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:26,586
Your mom is the most amazing.

260
00:24:32,601 --> 00:24:34,276
Eat up, Bao.

261
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,730
You eat too, Bao.

262
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:45,621
Eat.

263
00:24:45,621 --> 00:24:47,500
This beef ball is so hot.

264
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:49,856
Here, eat this.

265
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,520
Bao is a good kid.

266
00:25:29,661 --> 00:25:32,476
He's always wanted to call me Mom.

267
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,523
But I wouldn't let him.

268
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:39,476
So he keeps holding it back.

269
00:25:40,601 --> 00:25:43,366
You know I used to study dance.

270
00:25:45,321 --> 00:25:47,380
I loved dancing.

271
00:25:49,321 --> 00:25:52,559
But when I gave birth,
the delivery tore me badly.

272
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,639
Even walking was hard.

273
00:25:56,240 --> 00:26:00,160
Later, I had to work hard to raise him.

274
00:26:00,980 --> 00:26:03,496
How could I keep dancing?

275
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:07,720
But I don't regret having him at all.

276
00:26:13,581 --> 00:26:16,913
It's just that
sometimes I can't help being scared.

277
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:21,220
He's still so little.

278
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:23,680
He doesn't understand any of this.

279
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:28,301
When he grows up, when he goes to school,

280
00:26:28,301 --> 00:26:33,316
gets a job, and starts a family,

281
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:36,266
do you think...

282
00:26:39,461 --> 00:26:41,506
he'll blame me?

283
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:50,601
You've done a great job.

284
00:26:50,601 --> 00:26:55,686
At least, Bao has always known he's loved.

285
00:26:57,260 --> 00:27:00,196
He'll have a happy childhood.

286
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:08,280
If my mom had been more like you
when I was a kid,

287
00:27:09,821 --> 00:27:12,806
I probably would've been happier too.

288
00:28:04,641 --> 00:28:07,280
<i>What did you tell me to get me to Teng City?</i>

289
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:10,200
<i>You said you'd marry me and find me a job.</i>

290
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,881
<i>It's been four years.</i>

291
00:28:11,881 --> 00:28:14,520
<i>So where's that job you found me?</i>

292
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,840
<i>We're just not talking about that now?</i>

293
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:19,200
<i>Look at the way you are.</i>

294
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:22,200
<i>When my daughter and I came here,
you couldn't do enough for us.</i>

295
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:24,760
<i>I cook every day. You cooked only one meal!</i>

296
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:27,000
<i>What am I to you, your maid?</i>

297
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:30,593
<i>You won't get me a job,
so I stay home and wait on you.</i>

298
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,502
<i>So loud.</i>

299
00:30:02,761 --> 00:30:04,581
Morning.

300
00:30:04,581 --> 00:30:06,373
Have some breakfast.

301
00:30:20,841 --> 00:30:24,000
This place makes pretty good soy milk.

302
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,616
Have some more since you like it.

303
00:30:39,901 --> 00:30:44,803
- When did Tu Li leave?
- She left at dawn. She had to open the shop.

304
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:50,833
Why didn't you tell me about Wei Ming Zhen?

305
00:31:00,180 --> 00:31:02,310
I didn't want to affect you.

306
00:31:04,881 --> 00:31:07,115
- She--
- Next holiday,

307
00:31:07,115 --> 00:31:09,520
I'll go back to Jiang City with her.

308
00:31:10,161 --> 00:31:13,820
She wasn't there when I was little,
and I won't be there when she's old.

309
00:31:13,820 --> 00:31:16,540
Neither of us owes the other anything.

310
00:31:18,081 --> 00:31:19,488
I'll go with you.

311
00:31:19,488 --> 00:31:21,073
We'll see.

312
00:31:27,561 --> 00:31:31,138
Do you want to move back in?

313
00:31:40,927 --> 00:31:42,619
We'll see.

314
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,246
Eat it.

315
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,871
[Haoyun Logistics]

316
00:32:13,561 --> 00:32:15,793
We'll leave the rest to you.

317
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:28,440
Their files don't quite match the facts.

318
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,520
Word came from Lingang.

319
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:33,121
Baiyou's cash flow is in trouble.

320
00:32:33,121 --> 00:32:35,161
Some minor shareholders are selling.

321
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:39,561
And you put your name down at the worst time.

322
00:32:39,561 --> 00:32:41,820
They'll keep their eyes on you.

323
00:32:41,820 --> 00:32:44,214
Liu Bin Bo.

324
00:32:44,214 --> 00:32:46,200
What is it?

325
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:49,330
I saw him having dinner
with Zhang Bin at Haoting.

326
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:55,280
Baiyou and Haoyun have financial dealings.
It makes sense they'd meet in Teng City.

327
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:56,440
But we still need to confirm it.

328
00:32:56,440 --> 00:33:00,583
Check if the third party's dealings
with the auditee are aboveboard.

329
00:33:10,361 --> 00:33:12,780
<i>If it's just business,</i>

330
00:33:12,780 --> 00:33:17,343
<i>why did they invite Chen Yi
before he had even joined Haoyun?</i>

331
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:21,640
We do need to go there.

332
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,901
Ma Yang and I should go.
You're drawing too much attention now.

333
00:33:23,901 --> 00:33:25,061
It's not safe.

334
00:33:25,061 --> 00:33:27,193
I'll go with you.

335
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:31,860
Fine, but Lingang takes three to five days.

336
00:33:31,860 --> 00:33:34,700
- Is that okay with you?
- I'll have Xiao Yu book the tickets.

337
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:39,750
This isn't just about reporting to Hongshen.
It's important to me, too.

338
00:33:42,914 --> 00:33:46,592
I hope this is the break we need
to end all this soon.

339
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:32,370
[Once I can take some annual leave,
let's go back to Jiang City together.]

340
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:33,159
[Lingang]

341
00:35:33,159 --> 00:35:38,430
[Baiyou]

342
00:35:40,340 --> 00:35:42,821
It also feels really nice to the touch.

343
00:35:42,821 --> 00:35:45,301
Take a look. It'd be great for a child.

344
00:35:45,301 --> 00:35:48,720
- Let's go over here and pick another one.
- Pick one.

345
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:58,666
That's 38 yuan in total.

346
00:36:02,261 --> 00:36:04,486
The code is different.

347
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:10,820
Hi. Would you like me to show you around?

348
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:12,701
Hi. I have a question.

349
00:36:12,701 --> 00:36:14,600
What does the code on this toy mean?

350
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:16,440
I'd like to know exactly what it's made of.

351
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:20,660
The first digit indicates the production line.

352
00:36:20,660 --> 00:36:22,681
For example, the one you have is line four.

353
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:26,500
Our company currently operates
six production lines in Lingang and Teng City.

354
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:28,580
As for the materials,
they are all 3C-certified.

355
00:36:28,580 --> 00:36:31,116
They're baby-grade and skin-friendly.

356
00:36:31,116 --> 00:36:32,740
Okay, we'll look around a bit more.

357
00:36:32,740 --> 00:36:34,513
Sure.

358
00:36:39,221 --> 00:36:40,920
How's it going?

359
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:44,069
Any recent progress?

360
00:36:45,300 --> 00:36:46,901
Since the last report,

361
00:36:46,901 --> 00:36:50,181
we've completed due diligence
on every subsidiary under the group.

362
00:36:50,181 --> 00:36:53,060
We found no risk of material misstatements
in the financial statements.

363
00:36:53,060 --> 00:36:54,660
The report will be issued next week.

364
00:36:54,660 --> 00:36:57,681
Only Haoyun still hasn't been fully reviewed.

365
00:36:57,681 --> 00:37:01,780
We're waiting on some financial data.
They still need to submit it.

366
00:37:01,780 --> 00:37:05,128
When do you expect the results?

367
00:37:06,660 --> 00:37:09,421
We'll work overtime and push it through.

368
00:37:09,421 --> 00:37:11,246
We expect it next month.

369
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:13,840
Okay.

370
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,640
Thanks for your hard work.

371
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:19,036
Don't forget to come to dinner tonight.

372
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:25,528
[Haoyun Logistics]

373
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:16,920
[Miao Jing's Coming Home]

374
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:07,379
[Miao Jing's Coming Home]

375
00:40:03,620 --> 00:40:05,720
Where's Yi?

376
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:09,486
Wasn't Yi with you in the office just now?

377
00:40:30,821 --> 00:40:32,473
What's wrong?

378
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,221
Tell me.

379
00:40:35,221 --> 00:40:39,241
Since Miao Jing left on her trip,
why has time been moving so slowly?

380
00:40:39,241 --> 00:40:41,361
It's been dragging.

381
00:40:41,361 --> 00:40:43,216
Seriously dragging.

382
00:40:43,216 --> 00:40:44,900
No, I was...

383
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:49,000
I was asking whether you got
into her social media page.

384
00:40:52,261 --> 00:40:54,216
Did you fight again?

385
00:40:54,216 --> 00:40:55,640
You can ask me for advice!

386
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:59,600
Right now, you have a married man right here.

387
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:01,063
Go ahead.

388
00:41:05,701 --> 00:41:07,433
If it were you,

389
00:41:08,181 --> 00:41:10,861
what would you do if you and Li Qiao fought?

390
00:41:10,861 --> 00:41:11,940
Make it up to her.

391
00:41:11,940 --> 00:41:13,741
If that doesn't work, keep trying.

392
00:41:13,741 --> 00:41:17,500
Buy her a bag, makeup, something like that.

393
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:20,060
Do whatever it takes to make it up to her.

394
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:23,020
Miao Jing doesn't care about that stuff.

395
00:41:23,020 --> 00:41:27,360
Besides, my taste isn't exactly great.

396
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,336
Do you think it's about the money?

397
00:41:30,281 --> 00:41:31,421
It's about you.

398
00:41:31,421 --> 00:41:35,540
It's about
showing you're willing to grovel, right?

399
00:41:35,540 --> 00:41:37,640
- Who's there?
- What are you teaching him now?

400
00:41:37,640 --> 00:41:39,361
I'm not teaching him.

401
00:41:39,361 --> 00:41:40,980
Yi, don't listen to his nonsense.

402
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:42,660
Come eat at my place. The food's ready.

403
00:41:42,660 --> 00:41:44,176
- Yeah.
- Okay.

